</p>
<p>the deaths of 13 women and critical condition of 70 others. The procedures were 
</p>
<p>reportedly performed without free and informed consent, in facilities of deplorable 
</p>
<p>and unhygienic conditions, and with sub-standard clinical procedures. Women of low 
</p>
<p>socio-economic standing were actively targeted and incentivised by the State 
</p>
<p>Government of Chhattisgarh to undergo the sterilisation procedure, and there was a 
</p>
<p>general lack of information regarding the consequences and risks of the sterilisation. 
