<p><b>Yugoslav 
</b></p>
<p><b>Republic of 
</b></p>
<p><b>Macedonia  
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Arbitrary 
</b></p>
<p><b>detention;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Health;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Migrants;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Torture;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Allegations concerning the arbitrary detention of irregular migrants and asylum 
</p>
<p>seekers, including children, at the Reception Centre for Foreigners &#8220;Gazi Baba&#8221; in 
</p>
<p>Skopje. According to the information received, &#8220;Gazi Baba&#8221; has an official capacity 
</p>
<p>of up to 150 people but currently holds approximately 350 detainees. These irregular 
</p>
<p>migrants and asylum seekers are reportedly arbitrarily detained, sometimes for more 
</p>
<p>than six months, without the possibility to challenge their detention in a court of law. 
</p>
<p>Furthermore, detainees receive infrequent meals and some have to sleep on the floor. 
</p>
<p>Migrants and asylum seekers suffer from medical problems caused or aggravated by 
</p>
<p>the substandard conditions, the length of detention and the lack of consistent or 
</p>
<p>adequate medical assistance. More specifically, overcrowding, unsanitary conditions, 
</p>
<p>inadequate heating, insufficient quantities of hot water and the lack of ventilation were 
</p>
<p>mentioned as factors that contribute to the outbreak and spread of respiratory, 
</p>
<p>gastrointestinal and dermatological diseases.  
</p>
<p>08/07/2015 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
