<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Sale of children;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Allegations concerning numerous reported cases of sexual abuse and exploitation of 
</p>
<p>children committed in various regions of the United Kingdom. According to the 
</p>
<p>information received, between 1997 and 2014, numerous reported cases of sexual 
</p>
<p>abuse and exploitation throughout the United Kingdom were improperly investigated 
</p>
<p>by the authorities due partly to a culture of denial. Child victims were allegedly 
</p>
<p>treated with contempt, re-victimized and did not receive the appropriate care required 
</p>
<p>in such cases of sexual exploitation. Budget cuts to front line services have reportedly 
</p>
<p>weakened the response available for child victims of sexual exploitation. General 
</p>
<p>concerns are raised regarding the accountability of perpetrators and redress given to 
</p>
<p>victims.   
</p>
<p>18/06/2015 
</p>
