<p><b>Racism;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged imminent forced eviction of 53 members of a Roma community from their 
</p>
<p>settlement in the city of Irkutsk, Russian Federation. According to the information 
</p>
<p>received, 53 members of a Roma community in Irkutsk, including 34 minors, were 
</p>
<p>facing imminent forced eviction on 15 May 2015. Concern is expressed that the 
</p>
<p>eviction may be the result of discriminatory practices against Roma people in the 
</p>
<p>region, that the impact of the eviction was not been properly assessed and that 
</p>
<p>alternatives to eviction, including strategies for minimizing harm, had not been fully 
</p>
<p>explored.  
